messages.message:
Hey folks,

Took a pass to refactor the AIHub postman collection
https://www.postman.com/instabase/workspace/instabase-aihub/documentation/1498156-4049b657-0929-472d-95b7-70dba22b45c4

Made a number of changes:
1. Using API_ROOT instead of API_BASE to sync with docs.
2. Removed separate Commercial/Community environments. The most common use case for environments is when you have a DEV,UAT,PROD and need different url/token variables for each.
3. Added path variables to APIs that needed them. We have global variables (for example in app run by ID APIs) and in upload file APIs, made these path variables.
4. Added documentation for a number of variables and sections. Shows creator as Instabase instead of interstellar.

Will send out a PR to update soon to update the docs to this collection. This will be the official collection.
@Anil, when ready, would you get me the updated link so that I can adjust it in docs? It’s a quick fix.
@jean I merged in the docs PR - @Rosie approved it :slightly_smiling_face:
Oh, look at that, thank you so much @Anil!
Okay, I’ve cherry-picked to prod and re-kicked the docs, so the change should be live in the next 5 minutes or so.
